attribs.name: repeating_trait_-KJWWwiNOSYW3HKLFmXI_freetext
attribs.current: You gain the ability to channel divine energy directly from your deity, using that energy to fuel magical effects. You start with two such effects: Turn Undead and an effect determined by your domain. Some domains grant you additional effects as you advance in levels, as noted in the domain description

attribs.name: repeating_trait_-KJWWwiNOSYW3HKLFmXI_display_text
attribs.current: You gain the ability to channel divine energy directly from your deity, using that energy to fuel magical effects. You start with two such effects: Turn Undead and an effect determined by your domain. Some domains grant you additional effects as you advance in levels, as noted in the domain description

attribs.name: repeating_trait_-KJWWwiOo3K3kxmN3BAp_freetext
attribs.current:
As an action, you present your holy symbol and speak a prayer censuring the undead. Each undead that can see or hear you within 30 feet of you must make a Wisdom saving throw. If the creature fails its saving throw, it is turned for 1 minute or until it takes any damage.
A turned creature must spend its turns trying to move as far away from you as it can, and it can't willingly move to a space within 30 feet of you. It also can't take reactions. For its action, it can use only the Dash action or try to escape from an effect that prevents it from moving. If there's nowhere to move, the creature can use the Dodge action.

attribs.name: repeating_trait_-KJWWwiOo3K3kxmN3BAp_display_text

A turned creature must spend its turns trying to move as far away from you as it can, and it can't willingly move to a space within 30 feet of you. It also can't take reactions. For its action, it can use only the Dash action or try to escape from an effect that prevents it from moving. If there's nowhere to move, the creature can use the Dodge action.
When an undead fails its saving throw against your Turn Undead feature, the creature is instantly destroyed if its challenge rating is 1/2 or lower

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJWZJbvdaSKqg7qcNru_content
attribs.current:
You touch one object that is no larger than 10 feet in any dimension. Until the spell ends, the object sheds bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. The light can be colored as you like. Completely covering the object with something opaque blocks the light. The spell ends if you cast it again or dismiss it as an action.

If you target an object held or worn by a hostile creature, that creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw to avoid the spell.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJWZSIrNZmNDEMwcQtx_content
attribs.current:
A 60-foot-radius sphere of light spreads out from a point you choose within range. The sphere is bright light and sheds dim light for an additional 60 feet.

If you chose a point on an object you are holding or one that isn't being worn or carried, the light shines from the object with and moves with it. Completely covering the affected object with an opaque object, such as a bowl or a helm, blocks the light.

If any of this spell's area overlaps with an area of darkness created by a spell of or lower, the spell that created the darkness is dispelled.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJWZXsOwYaQaeCN8upZ_content
attribs.current: You touch a creature and can end either one disease or one condition afflicting it. The condition can be blinded, deafened, paralyzed, or poisoned.

attribs.name: flaws
attribs.current:
Caged life was simple. I am incapable of adulting. Dealing with the scope and complexity of freedom is too difficult, and I depend too much on my brother.

She feels disgusting and ugly without her wings, and won't even consider a romantic relationship.

attribs.name: personality_traits
attribs.current:
I was tortured but at the same time spoiled. This bipolar lifestyle makes me avoid behaviors and habits that remind me of that time. I have been trained to be a refined lady, so instead, I publicly act crude and animalistic. 

She can only be herself with her brother Tak. With him, she can cry and dream and rest.

attribs.name: ideals
attribs.current: Vengeance. Eye for an eye. There's no true value in judging goodness or evil. There's fault and there's penance for those mistakes.

attribs.name: bonds
attribs.current: My brother (followed by vengeance) is my life.  I might give him grief, but I will kill and die for him.

attribs.name: miscellaneous_notes
attribs.current: Feature - Never Again:  You have spend your entire life trying to escape and no one will ever keep you now. Whenever you come upon a confinement, whether yours or another's, you immediately spot the weakest point in it and know how to exploit it.

attribs.name: proficiencies
attribs.current: Flute, martial weapons, all armor, shields, all simple weapons

attribs.current: When you roll initiative, use your reaction to give self or a creature w/in 60' that you can see +2 bonus to initiative for each psi point spent.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJZyjLIAFjnqBWlHhJj_content
attribs.current: A shimmering field appears and surrounds a creature of your choice within range, granting it a +2 bonus to AC for the duration.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJaQ8QRBAq0p4KOvnZ2_content
attribs.current:
Cost: 2 psi points

As a bonus action, you increase your speed by 30 feet until the end of your turn. Also, you don't provoke opportunity attacks this turn.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJaQdaU8S3ZSvqVYdWD_content
attribs.current: While focused on this discipline, you charge one nonmagical weapon you carry, or one of your fists, with psionic energy. Attacks you make with it are considered magical and have a +1 bonus to attack rolls and damage rolls.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJi8S43eMeXx4hML76U_content
attribs.current:
Cost: 1 psi point

Momentarily transform a weapon you hold into psionic energy. Next attack requires no attack roll. Instead, target makes a Dexterity saving throw against this discipline. Failed save, target takes attack's normal damage and suffers any additional effects. Successful save, target takes half damage from the attack but suffers no additional effects that would normally be imposed on a hit.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiAGSXZNnBN2KmTDjV_content
attribs.current: When you hit a target with a melee weapon attack, you can increase the damage to that target. Target takes an extra 1d10 psychic damage for each psi point you spend.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiAtjvFFkoIV-G4cKv_content
attribs.current: Psychically strike one creature. 2d8 at 5th level.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiBZ95JIbLPJtzVuxA_content
attribs.current: Alter own density and weight to improve mobility. Walking speed increases by 10 feet, and the next time you stand up, you need to spend no more than 10 feet of movement to do so.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiBsI7GuZkLWcipDZ0_content
attribs.current: Communicate telepathically with one creature you can see. Do not need to share a language with a creature for it to understand your telepathic utterances, and the creature understand you even if it lacks a language. You can allow a creature to respond to you telepathically, but is must understand at least one language in order to communicate this way. This ability to communicate lasts until the start of your next turn. You can communicate with an unwilling creature.

attribs.name: repeating_trait_-KJiCzcxUPUb5atB0S9m_display_text
attribs.current: When using the Attack action, you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action.

attribs.name: repeating_trait_-KJiDB1zFww7fgbwozqb_display_text
attribs.current: Gain +10 to attack roll. Make this choice after rolling but before hit/miss determined.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiEYFuwC8CMK-cCzbZ_content
attribs.current:
Flame-like radiance descends on a creature that you can see within range. The target must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take 1d8 radiant damage. The target gains no benefit from cover for this saving throw.

The spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiEed9NbZ2aEZH3fQU_content
attribs.current: You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one ability check of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the ability check. The spell then ends.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiF-kKt4jq8Fysh-37_content
attribs.current: You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one saving throw of its choice. It can roll the die before or after the saving throw. The spell then ends.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiFFoKM3YCfiL2nKmN_content
attribs.current:
A creature you touch regains a number of hit points equal to 1d8 + your spellcasting ability modifier. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.

At Higher Levels: When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the healing increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 1st.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiKvRlbX5MmSXZx2U9_content
attribs.current:
This spell repairs a single break or tear in an object you touch, such as broken chain link, two halves of a broken key, a torn clack, or a leaking wineskin. As long as the break or tear is no larger than 1 foot in any dimension, you mend it, leaving no trace of the former damage.

This spell can physically repair a magic item or construct, but the spell can't restore magic to such an object.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiL36LMNJdudjynsZJ_content
attribs.current:
You bless up to three creatures of your choice within range. Whenever a target makes an attack roll or a saving throw before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to the attack roll or saving throw.

At Higher Levels: When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 1st.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiLOY6iGJ8bnucRx33_content
attribs.current:
Make a melee spell attack against a creature you can reach. On a hit, the target takes 3d10 necrotic damage.

At Higher Levels: When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d10 for each slot level above 1st.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiLYBqFtdiTdGvlWCI_content
attribs.current:
A flash of light streaks toward a creature of your choice within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target takes 4d6 radiant damage, and the next attack roll made against this target before the end of your next turn has advantage, thanks to the mystical dim light glittering on the target until then.

At Higher Levels: When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiLjhuSe0kMdHR8LXI_content
attribs.current:
A creature of your choice that you can see within range regains hit points equal to 1d4 + your spellcasting ability modifier. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.

At Higher Levels: When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the healing increases by 1d4 for each slot level above 1st.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiMj8z0BcgXDCcBqXp_materials
attribs.current: Specially marked sticks, bones, or similar tokens worth at least 25gp

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiMj8z0BcgXDCcBqXp_content
attribs.current:
By casting gem-inlaid sticks, rolling dragon bones, laying out ornate cards, or employing some other divining tool, you receive an omen from an otherworldly entity about the results of a specific course of action that you plan to take within the next 30 minutes. The DM chooses from the following possible omens.

 Weal, for good results

 Woe, for bad results

 Weal and woe, for both good and bad results

 Nothing, for results that aren't especially good or bad

The spell doesn't take into account any possible circumstances that might change the outcome, such as the casting of additional spells or the loss or gain of a companion.

If you cast the spell two or more times before completing your next long rest, there is a cumulative 25 percent chance for each casting after the first that you get a random reading. The DM makes this roll in secret.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiMyy-0QR5z4tq7O6Q_content
attribs.current:
Up to six creatures of your choice that you can see within range each regain hit points equal to 2d8 + your spellcasting ability modifier. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.

At Higher Levels: When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the healing increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 2nd.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiNfppRhBPDQ9ZNzYl_content
attribs.current:
You create a floating, spectral weapon within range that lasts for the duration or until you cast this spell again. When you cast the spell, you can make a melee spell attack against a creature within 5 feet of the weapon. On a hit, the target takes force damage equal to 1d8 + your spellcasting ability modifier.

As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the weapon up to 20 feet and repeat the attack against a creature within 5 feet of it.

The weapon can take whatever form you choose. Clerics of deities who are associated with a particular weapon (as St. Cuthbert is known for his mace and Thor for his hammer) make this spell's effect resemble that weapon.

At Higher Levels: When you cast this spell using a spell slot 3rd level of or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for every two slot levels above the 2nd.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiOHjMCdYL3XvfZEmN_materials
attribs.current: A pinch of salt and one copper piece placed on each of the corpse's eyes, which must remain there for the duration

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiOHjMCdYL3XvfZEmN_content
attribs.current:
You touch a corpse or other remains. For the duration, the target is protected from decay and can't become undead.

The spell also effectively extends the time limit on raising the target from the dead, since days spent under the influence of this spell don't count against the time limit of spells such as raise dead.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiOKExMzbKz4q3rl0c_materials
attribs.current: A tiny strip of white cloth

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KJiOKExMzbKz4q3rl0c_content
attribs.current:
Your spell bolsters your allies with toughness and resolve. Choose up to three creatures within range. Each target's hit point maximum and current hit points increase by 5 for the duration.

At Higher Levels: When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, a target's hit points increase by an additional 5 for each slot level above 2nd.

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KK4t-UszaJU-Onu2j2Z_materials
attribs.current: A pair of platinum rings worth at least 50gp each, which you and the target must wear for the duration

attribs.name: repeating_spell_-KK4t-UszaJU-Onu2j2Z_content
attribs.current:
This spell wards a willing creature you touch and creates a mystic connection between you and the target until the spell ends. While the target is within 60 feet of you, it gains a +1 bonus to AC and saving throws, and it has resistance to all damage. Also, each time it takes damage, you take the same amount of damage.

The spell ends if you drop to 0 hit points or if you and the target become separated by more than 60 feet. It also ends if the spell is cast again on either of the connected creatures. You can also dismiss the spell as an action.
